The paper deals with feature engineering for relational data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a deep neural network approach for automatically learning appropriate transformations of relational data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses heuristics-based approaches for feature engineering, which can be considered as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments with Kaggle competitions, which involve natural language processing tasks (cs.CL) and social network analysis (cs.SI).
